    <introduction>
      <para>This plug-in is used to add all assemblies found in a given folder and its sub-folders as references
to use when generating reflection information.</para>
    </introduction>

<section>
  <title>Configuration Options</title>
  <content>
    <para>The configuration options consist of a list of wildcard reference paths that will be scanned for
assemblies to pass to the <application>MRefBuilder</application> tool at build time.  Each entry consists
of a path and a wildcard (<localUri>*.dll</localUri> by default).  The default is to recurse into all
sub-folders as well.  This can be turned off by setting the <codeInline>Recurse</codeInline> property on
the entry to False.</para>
  </content>
</section>

